parameters: \C[6]One Sabbath Jesus was teaching in a synagogue.
\C[6]A woman there had an evil spirit that had kept
her sick for eighteen years; she was bent over
and could not straighten up at all.
\C[6]When Jesus saw her, he called out to her:
Woman, you are free from your sickness!
\C[6]He placed his hands on her, and at once she
straightened herself up and praised God.

\C[6]The official of the synagogue was angry that
Jesus had healed on the Sabbath, so he spoke up
There are six days in which we should work;
so come during those days and be healed,
You hypocrites! Any one of you would untie your
ox or your donkey from the stall and take it
out to give it water on the Sabbath.
Now here is this descendant of Abraham whom
Satan has kept in bonds for eighteen years;
should she not be released on the Sabbath?
\C[6]His answer made his enemies ashamed of
themselves, while the people rejoiced over all
the wonderful things that he did.
\C[6]Pero el jefe de la sinagoga, enojado
porque Jesús la había sanado en sábado,

Pues a esta mujer, que es descendiente de

no se la debía desatar aunque fuera en sábado?
\C[6]Cuando Jesús dijo esto, sus enemigos quedaron
avergonzados; pero toda la gente se alegraba
viendo las grandes cosas que él hacía.
\C[6]Però el cap de la sinagoga, indignat perquè
Jesús havia curat en dissabte, deia a la gent:
Hi ha sis dies per a treballar. Veniu a fer-vos
curar un d'aquests dies i no en dissabte.
Hipòcrites! ¿No és veritat que també en
dissabte tots deslligueu el bou i l'ase de
l'estable i els porteu a l'abeurador?
No calia, doncs, precisament en dissabte,
deslligar aquesta filla d'Abraham que Satanàs
tenia subjectada des de feia divuit anys?
